  "title": "Staff Nurse (Home Care) x5 | Mon–Fri | Up to $4,500 + Allowances | No Shifts",
  "description": "<p>💼 Job Type: Full-Time</p><p>Palliative Care - 3 positions</p><p>Chronic Illness Home Care - 2 positions</p><p>📍 Location: Islandwide</p><p>🕒 Work Schedule: Mon to Fri | 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM</p><p>💰 Salary Range: Up to $4,500 per month</p><p>🎁 Allowances: On-call allowance + Fixed monthly nursing\nallowance<br /></p><p><strong>✨ About the Role</strong></p><p>Join our dedicated Home Care Nursing Team, where\nyou’ll play an essential role in ensuring comfort, dignity, and quality of life for patients with chronic illnesses in the comfort of their homes. This role focuses on holistic care, ensuring patients receive consistent support and improved quality of life.</p><p><strong>👩‍⚕️ Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>• Conduct home visits for patients with chronic\nillnesses</p><p>• Perform comprehensive nursing assessments and\ncoordinate with doctors for follow-ups</p><p>• Monitor medication compliance and support patients\nin managing long-term conditions</p><p>• Perform nursing procedures such as wound dressing,\ncatheter insertion, and NGT care</p><p>• Initiate, review, and implement individualized\nnursing care plans</p><p>• Maintain accurate documentation and update records\nin the IT system</p><p>• Identify and refer patients/families for financial\nor psychological support when needed</p><p>• Participate in community activities when required</p><p><strong>🌟 What We’re Looking For</strong></p><p>Palliative Care - 3 positions</p><p>• Min 3 years nursing experience</p><p>• Diploma/Degree in Nursing or equivalent</p><p>• Registered Nurse with the Singapore Nursing Board (SNB)</p><p>• Possess a Nursing Certificate in Palliative Care</p><p>• Compassionate, patient, and able to work independently with strong communication and assessment skills</p><p><br />Chronic Illness Home Care - 2 positions</p><p>• Min 1 year nursing experience</p><p>• Diploma/Degree in Nursing or equivalent</p><p>• Registered Nurse with the Singapore Nursing Board (SNB)</p><p>• Compassionate, patient, and able to work independently with strong communication and assessment skills</p><p><strong>🎯 What We Offer</strong></p><p>• Competitive salary: Up to $4,500 per month +\nAllowances</p><p>• 5-day work week (Mon–Fri, no weekends)</p><p>• Opportunities for professional growth and meaningful\ncommunity work</p><p>• Supportive and collaborative working environment<br /></p><p><strong>📩 Interested? Apply Now!</strong></p><p>Send your resume in MS Word format to:\n<strong>Vanessa.chua@crew.sg</strong></p><p>Please include your <strong>availability, notice period, and expected salary.</strong></p><p><em>* Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em><br /></p><p>Vanessa Chua Peng Teng (R25158315)</p><p>HRnet Ventures Pte Ltd - CREW by HRnet</p><p>E.A. 24C2435</p>",
